  "abstract": "The scale of this map is approximately 1:31,000 (40 chains per inch). It shows the names of lot owners for the town. It was compiled by Charles Unwin, Provincial Land Surveyor, Provincial Chambers, Toronto and lithographed by J. Ellis, Toronto, C. W.<div><br /></div><div>This map was manually georeferenced using ArcGIS Pro’s Georeference Tool. Due to the age of the plan and the nature of the georeferencing, there are known errors. However, the methods used were done to ensure best fit across the entire plan. This imagery is not intended to be used as general reference only, and measurements taken from this plan are not considered accurate.<br /><div><br /></div><div>For historical maps of Toronto from other years, please refer to the following:</div><div><ul><li><a href='https://www.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=aa07fde8ffd94c18916a97594cab65ff' target='_blank' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'>1818</a><br /></li><li><a href='https://www.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=dcd746c9eeed4c17895706998c851c05' target='_blank' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'>1880</a><br /></li><li><a href='https://www.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=352d589e35454761a75dc6d9e01e6459' target='_blank' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'>1858</a><br /></li><li><a href='https://www.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=54ec5da045f54280a3af3f3ead4b7420' target='_blank' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'>1889</a><br /></li><li><a href='https://www.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=0936065c2a68417db81c89e723380310' target='_blank' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'>1903</a><br /></li><li><a href='https://www.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=9ff1c100a0eb4047955ad5d839987dff' target='_blank' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'>1913</a><br /></li><li><a href='https://www.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=5791f2e39099497dabd6fe1af983b7a6' target='_blank' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'>1924</a><br /></li></ul></div></div>",
